### =====================================================================
### Smart Campus Hub - Module C (Tickets)
### VS Code REST Client format - install the "REST Client" extension
###
### Workflow:
###   1. Run the Login request first - the response gives you the token.
###   2. Copy the token into the @token variable below.
###   3. Optionally fill @ticketId and @technicianId after creating them.
### =====================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@email = admin@campus.lk
@password = Test1234

# Paste from the Login response
@token = PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

# Paste after creating a ticket / promoting a technician in MongoDB
@ticketId = PASTE_TICKET_ID_HERE
@technicianId = PASTE_TECHNICIAN_USER_ID_HERE
@commentId = PASTE_COMMENT_ID_HERE


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. Login - copy "data.token" from the response into @token above
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. Create a ticket (no attachments) - simplest happy path
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----RestClientBoundary

------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Projector dead
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Lamp burned out during the morning lecture
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

IT_EQUIPMENT
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="priority"

HIGH
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="contactDetails"

admin@campus.lk
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="location"

Block A, Lab 3
------RestClientBoundary--


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. List my tickets
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/my
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. List tickets assigned to me (technician view)
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/assigned
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. List ALL tickets (admin only)
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5b. List ALL tickets filtered by status
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets?status=OPEN
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Get a single ticket by id
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 7. Admin assigns a technician (OPEN -> ASSIGNED)
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/assign
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "technicianId": "{{technicianId}}"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 8. Technician starts work (ASSIGNED -> IN_PROGRESS)
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 9. Technician marks resolved (IN_PROGRESS -> RESOLVED)
### Resolution notes are required.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "RESOLVED",
  "resolutionNotes": "Replaced the projector lamp"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 10. Owner closes the ticket (RESOLVED -> CLOSED)
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CLOSED"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 11. Owner re-opens the ticket (RESOLVED -> IN_PROGRESS)
### Use this INSTEAD of #10 if the issue is not really fixed.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 12. Admin rejects a ticket - reason is required
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "REJECTED",
  "rejectionReason": "Duplicate of an earlier ticket"
}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 13. Delete a ticket (owner-OPEN-only or admin always)
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 14. Download an attachment - replace FILENAME with the real one
### from the ticket's attachmentUrls list
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/attachments/REPLACE_FILENAME.png
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### =====================================================================
### Comments
### =====================================================================

### List comments on a ticket
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Add a comment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Looking into this now."
}


### Edit a comment (author only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/comments/{{commentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Updated - I have ordered a new lamp."
}


### Delete a comment (author or admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/comments/{{commentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### =====================================================================
### Negative tests - useful when writing the test evidence section of
### the report. These SHOULD fail with the noted status code.
### =====================================================================

### Should fail 401 - no token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/my


### Should fail 403 - normal user cannot list ALL tickets
### (run after logging in as a USER, not ADMIN)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### Should fail 400 - missing title
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----RestClientBoundary

------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

No title set
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

OTHER
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="priority"

LOW
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="contactDetails"

x@y.com
------RestClientBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="location"

somewhere
------RestClientBoundary--


### Should fail 400 - resolve without notes
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "RESOLVED"
}


### Should fail 400 - reject without reason
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/{{ticketId}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "REJECTED"
}
